          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Reactions O-17(n,p)N-17 and O-18(n,d)N-17 with reactor",
                "neutrons"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "REAC"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Israel swimming pool reactor at Soreq"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The fast spectrum at the end of the pneumatic transfer",
                "tube at the core face of the reactor was 1.21*10**12",
                "n/cm2*sec."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Activation",
                "The fission neutron spectrum averaged cross-sections",
                "were measured by counting the delayed neutron emission",
                "of irradiated water samples enriched with oxygen-17 and",
                "-18. Nitrogen-17, the delayed-neutron precursor, decays",
                "by beta- emission to excited states of oxygen-17 which",
                "desintegrate instantaneously into oxygen-16 and a",
                "neutron. It was assumed that nitrogen-17 decays",
                "entirely through neutron emission and that the",
                "neutrons belong to two energy groups = 1.22 MeV(61.5%",
                "and 0.426 MeV(38.5%)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PROPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " the neutron emission was measured in a 4Pi",
                "geometry counting assembly consisting of 6 BF3",
                "proportional neutron counters. The counting efficiency",
                "was determined with calibrated radioactive neutron",
                "sources over the range of 0.2 To 4.5 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The results obtained from the five samples were",
                "analysed using the following equation=",
                "      n = m(17)*Y(17) + m(18)*y(18) where",
                "    - n is the net neutron count of the sample",
                "    - m(17) and m(18) are the respective contents of",
                "       O-17 and O-18 in the sample in gram atoms.",
                "    - y(17) and y(18) are the yields of delayed",
                "       neutrons per gram atom from O-17(n,p) and",
                "       O-18(n,d) respectively.",
                "Least squares fit analysis was used to determine the",
                "two yields y(17) and y(18)"
              ]
            }
          ],
